Rui Sousa wrote:
> So I would suggest either always use a 32 bytes alignment for the tasklet list
> or state in the config help file that the 586 option is no longer forward
> compatible in SMP systems.
huh?
* if you don't have the right command line options set, bad things will
happen, and
* your statement about compatibility makes no sense.  There is NO binary
module compatibility, because critical kernel structures change with
compiler and kernel options.
